$ Outlook: Message -> Clipboard -> Paste

The *Paste* button allows to paste
  • keeping the source formatting
  • merging formattings
  • keeping text only
  • pasting specially
  • setting default paste
  

*Set Default Paste…* takes the user to
→ Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Mail/Compose-messages/Editor-options/Advanced[File -> Options -> Mail -> Compose messages -> Editor options -> Advanced] from where
he can go to → Microsoft/Office/Outlook/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Mail/Compose-messages/Editor-options/Advanced/Cut-copy-and-paste[Cut, copy, and paste] to
set permanent pasting options.
